3. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper uses statistical methods and central limit theorems to analyze the power of A/B testing under interference. This is a key area of research in data structures and algorithms. 
4. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper's focus on quantifying the power of A/B testing as a function of the number of exposed individuals is related to information theory. 
5. cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) - The paper's focus on interference and its impact on A/B testing is relevant to the study of multiagent systems, where agents may interact and interfere with each other's actions.
